1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:00:20,150 --> 00:00:22,510
I want us to be together again.

3
00:00:25,110 --> 00:00:27,750
You have talked to me for two years,

4
00:00:29,110 --> 00:00:31,430
though I haven't replied even once.

5
00:00:31,910 --> 00:00:34,020
From now on, no matter what will happen,

6
00:00:34,390 --> 00:00:36,550
I won't let you go.

7
00:00:36,830 --> 00:00:38,110
Give me your hand.

8
00:00:39,590 --> 00:00:40,590
Why doesn't it beat?

9
00:02:23,630 --> 00:02:25,710
Open the door, Tai!

10
00:02:25,950 --> 00:02:27,590
Tai, open the door!

11
00:02:27,590 --> 00:02:29,270
What?

12
00:02:29,990 --> 00:02:32,630
Tien, how did you get in here?

13
00:02:32,630 --> 00:02:35,870
This is your house. I am your brother. I duplicated the key.

14
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:37,470
Huh?

15
00:02:42,070 --> 00:02:43,950
I have something to ask you.

16
00:02:43,950 --> 00:02:45,630
And, I'm going to sleep over here.

17
00:02:45,630 --> 00:02:48,030
Get me the bedding.

18
00:02:55,590 --> 00:02:57,150
(Meow)

19
00:02:57,150 --> 00:02:58,990
Shit!

20
00:02:58,990 --> 00:03:00,550
What?

21
00:03:01,740 --> 00:03:03,150
A cat?

22
00:03:06,430 --> 00:03:08,110
Duer. It's ok.

23
00:03:08,110 --> 00:03:09,630
Come here.

24
00:03:10,910 --> 00:03:12,230
Yeah, it's my cat.

25
00:03:12,870 --> 00:03:14,790
I adopted it.

26
00:03:15,470 --> 00:03:16,470
Seriously?

27
00:03:16,860 --> 00:03:18,070
Yes.

28
00:03:18,070 --> 00:03:19,470
Look at its face.

29
00:03:20,550 --> 00:03:21,990
Isn't it a burden?

30
00:03:21,990 --> 00:03:24,790
It's my cat. I can take care of it.

31
00:03:27,630 --> 00:03:30,670
What are you here for? Just say it.

32
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:37,230
Well, let me see.

33
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:44,150
Well, now I just can't understand myself.

34
00:03:44,150 --> 00:03:46,910
I held one's hand.

35
00:03:46,910 --> 00:03:49,829
And, the world seemed stopped.

36
00:03:49,829 --> 00:03:50,790
Do you know what I mean?

37
00:03:51,190 --> 00:03:51,870
Yes.

38
00:03:51,870 --> 00:03:55,100
My heart beat so fast. I can't understand that.

39
00:03:55,670 --> 00:04:01,070
Then, I couldn't think of anything else except that.

40
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:03,430
You're in love!

41
00:04:04,550 --> 00:04:06,030
What?

42
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:11,700
So, you happened to hold one's hand, right?

43
00:04:12,310 --> 00:04:15,700
It made your heart beat so fast that you didn't know what to do.

44
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:19,390
Until now, you haven't been able to get it off your mind.

45
00:04:19,390 --> 00:04:21,190
Am I right?

46
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:25,670
Just as perfect as my bro should be.

47
00:04:25,670 --> 00:04:27,950
It's not just that.

48
00:04:27,950 --> 00:04:31,430
You may unknowingly fall in love with that person.

49
00:04:31,430 --> 00:04:34,430
Then, when you were holding hands,

50
00:04:34,950 --> 00:04:38,030
your subconsciousness...

51
00:04:38,030 --> 00:04:41,030
cannot control your feelings.

52
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:11,430
What the hell are you saying?

53
00:05:11,430 --> 00:05:13,750
You even haven't been in love.

54
00:05:16,350 --> 00:05:19,430
Well! Though I have not,

55
00:05:19,430 --> 00:05:23,670
I have written some articles about that.

56
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:26,430
I am good at writing these things.

57
00:05:34,870 --> 00:05:36,750
Brother...

58
00:05:37,830 --> 00:05:39,870
Tell me!

59
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:44,990
If you don't tell me, I swear I'll curse you

60
00:05:47,030 --> 00:05:49,710
that you will be sleepless tonight.

61
00:05:49,710 --> 00:05:51,550
Got it, bro?

62
00:05:53,110 --> 00:05:55,500
Are you here to make trouble with me?

63
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:57,870
It's all because of you.

64
00:05:57,870 --> 00:05:59,350
Come on! Just tell me!

65
00:06:11,710 --> 00:06:12,870
I met my soul mate.

66
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:14,270
God!

67
00:06:14,430 --> 00:06:16,350
We both know we are each other's soul mates.

68
00:06:20,230 --> 00:06:22,510
So, you know I am...

69
00:06:22,510 --> 00:06:24,550
You are my soul mate.

70
00:06:26,350 --> 00:06:29,350
You have talked to me for two years,

71
00:06:29,910 --> 00:06:34,230
though I haven't replied even once.

72
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:39,870
That's awesome!

73
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:41,150
Tai!

74
00:06:42,710 --> 00:06:46,510
Listen to me. I'm so proud of you.

75
00:06:46,510 --> 00:06:49,500
Finally, you talked to him.

76
00:06:50,230 --> 00:06:52,350
I know. You hurt me.

77
00:06:52,590 --> 00:06:54,110
Anyway, thanks.

78
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:57,750
How far do you guys go?

79
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:00,070
Like this...

80
00:07:01,190 --> 00:07:02,950
Or... this.

81
00:07:04,310 --> 00:07:05,670
Or...

82
00:07:09,150 --> 00:07:10,590
Stop that!

83
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:12,590
I just had a dinner with him.

84
00:07:12,590 --> 00:07:15,590
And he drove me home.

85
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:18,390
Oh!

86
00:07:19,190 --> 00:07:22,270
This is a great little step to my mind.

87
00:07:22,270 --> 00:07:26,590
Finally, you stopped letting your parents' affairs dominate your life.

88
00:07:27,910 --> 00:07:28,950
Who are you talking to?

89
00:07:31,510 --> 00:07:33,630
I'm talking to my delight.

90
00:07:35,230 --> 00:07:36,950
Okay. I'll give you two some privacy.

91
00:07:36,950 --> 00:07:37,620
I'm off to bed.

92
00:07:37,620 --> 00:07:38,630
Wow!

93
00:07:39,070 --> 00:07:40,870
You sleep so early.

94
00:07:41,710 --> 00:07:44,630
You'll know when you start working.

95
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:46,750
Don't you go to school tomorrow?

96
00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:48,670
The class is in the afternoon, so...

97
00:07:48,670 --> 00:07:51,060
Back to you, are you changing the topic now?

98
00:07:51,750 --> 00:07:52,790
Good night!

99
00:07:52,790 --> 00:07:54,220
I'm so sleepy.

100
00:07:54,670 --> 00:07:55,790
Hey!

101
00:07:56,830 --> 00:07:58,590
Have a sweet dream, bro.

102
00:08:06,270 --> 00:08:07,510
(Mumbling) Awesome!

103
00:08:18,790 --> 00:08:20,350
You're in love!

104
00:08:26,630 --> 00:08:27,790
(Mumbling) Holy shit.

105
00:08:32,270 --> 00:08:36,230
Tien, don't forget to

106
00:08:36,590 --> 00:08:39,030
lock the door and windows.

107
00:08:39,030 --> 00:08:43,190
Most importantly, don't ever let Duer out.

108
00:08:55,310 --> 00:08:56,510
Patts?

109
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:00,310
Hi.

110
00:09:12,790 --> 00:09:14,750
Are you here for me?

111
00:09:15,630 --> 00:09:16,870
Yes.

112
00:09:18,030 --> 00:09:21,030
Can I drive you to work?

113
00:09:21,670 --> 00:09:22,390
Yes?

114
00:09:22,390 --> 00:09:26,830
Your workplace and mine are close.

115
00:09:26,830 --> 00:09:30,750
So, I thought we could go together.

116
00:09:31,310 --> 00:09:35,470
Patts, what if I leave first today or don't have to go to work,

117
00:09:35,470 --> 00:09:36,830
what would you do?

118
00:09:38,110 --> 00:09:41,990
Well, I don't know.

119
00:09:42,670 --> 00:09:45,750
I don't have your number.

120
00:09:45,750 --> 00:09:48,070
And, it doesn't rain today.

121
00:09:48,070 --> 00:09:50,590
I don't know how to contact you.

122
00:09:52,350 --> 00:09:53,590
Shall we get in the car?

123
00:09:53,590 --> 00:09:54,990
We're going to be late.

124
00:09:57,110 --> 00:09:57,910
Okay.

125
00:10:00,990 --> 00:10:01,950
There you go.

126
00:10:01,950 --> 00:10:02,790
Thank you.

127
00:10:03,550 --> 00:10:04,870
Careful.

128
00:10:24,190 --> 00:10:25,150
Patts.

129
00:10:25,150 --> 00:10:26,030
Yes?

130
00:10:26,510 --> 00:10:28,070
Give me your phone.

131
00:10:31,470 --> 00:10:32,790
Here.

132
00:10:36,830 --> 00:10:38,550
Can I give you my number?

133
00:10:40,870 --> 00:10:42,350
Sure.

134
00:10:46,150 --> 00:10:47,190
Done.

135
00:10:47,390 --> 00:10:50,390
Can you put it over there?

136
00:10:51,070 --> 00:10:51,950
Ok.

137
00:10:58,110 --> 00:10:59,310
Patts.

138
00:10:59,830 --> 00:11:00,870
Yeah?

139
00:11:00,870 --> 00:11:04,790
From now on, if you want to do something with me,

140
00:11:04,790 --> 00:11:06,870
you can ask me first.

141
00:11:09,750 --> 00:11:11,030
Why?

142
00:11:11,430 --> 00:11:12,830
You don't like surprises?

143
00:11:12,830 --> 00:11:14,630
Not that.

144
00:11:14,630 --> 00:11:20,550
I don't want to enforce you

145
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:22,630
to do anything for me.

146
00:11:22,630 --> 00:11:24,540
I want you to be yourself.

147
00:11:24,540 --> 00:11:26,550
You don't have to change anything about yourself.

148
00:11:26,550 --> 00:11:28,630
Because I'll do the same.

149
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:33,270
Shall we get to know each other little by little?

150
00:11:33,910 --> 00:11:36,190
Sure. I agree.

151
00:11:37,590 --> 00:11:38,950
Okay.

152
00:11:40,350 --> 00:11:41,980
And, from now on...

153
00:11:43,550 --> 00:11:48,470
I'll make it all up to you for the two years you've lost.

154
00:11:51,430 --> 00:11:54,910
Can I hold your hand?

155
00:11:55,220 --> 00:11:58,230
That's a start for your compensate.

156
00:12:24,310 --> 00:12:25,830
-Saengtai. -Yes?

157
00:12:26,030 --> 00:12:29,030
Can I ask you to do something?

158
00:12:29,470 --> 00:12:34,350
I want to call you Tai.

159
00:12:34,350 --> 00:12:36,470
So, I can feel closer to you.

160
00:12:38,430 --> 00:12:39,630
Of course you can.

161
00:12:39,670 --> 00:12:42,670
You can call me whatever you want.

162
00:12:43,310 --> 00:12:44,870
All at your own convenience.

163
00:12:45,670 --> 00:12:47,110
Thank you so much.

164
00:12:48,990 --> 00:12:51,190
And, one more thing.

165
00:12:52,710 --> 00:12:55,870
Why hadn't you talked to me before?

166
00:13:01,230 --> 00:13:03,550
You don't have to tell me, if you don't want to do so.

167
00:13:08,230 --> 00:13:09,590
No, it's okay.

168
00:13:10,950 --> 00:13:13,070
To tell you the truth,

169
00:13:14,310 --> 00:13:16,740
my mom and dad are soul mates.

170
00:13:19,670 --> 00:13:21,710
But, they divorced.

171
00:13:22,870 --> 00:13:24,910
[Although I was confident that]

172
00:13:24,910 --> 00:13:28,270
[mom and dad were the luckiest couple in the world.]

173
00:13:29,550 --> 00:13:34,070
What I'm about to tell you is going to be hard for you.

174
00:13:34,070 --> 00:13:38,670
Your Mom and I decided to get a divorce.

175
00:13:39,310 --> 00:13:40,830
[At the day they left each other,]

176
00:13:40,830 --> 00:13:45,950
[they acted as if nothing had mattered.]

177
00:13:48,990 --> 00:13:50,590
Now that it comes down to this,

178
00:13:50,590 --> 00:13:52,630
you're really not going to say something?

179
00:13:55,390 --> 00:13:58,980
Even if I say something now, you won't understand.

180
00:13:59,350 --> 00:14:03,110
How can I understand as you didn't do it at all?

181
00:14:04,590 --> 00:14:05,700
Good!

182
00:14:07,550 --> 00:14:13,110
It's best... that you know nothing!

183
00:14:14,630 --> 00:14:15,870
Mom...

184
00:14:16,550 --> 00:14:17,870
Dad. Dad!

185
00:14:17,870 --> 00:14:19,310
Saengchan, don't.

186
00:14:19,310 --> 00:14:20,620
-Chan. -Dad!

187
00:14:20,950 --> 00:14:22,510
-Dad! Wait! -Tai!

188
00:14:28,910 --> 00:14:29,910
Why?

189
00:14:37,390 --> 00:14:38,750
-Dad! Dad! -Tai!

190
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:41,750
Dad! Dad!

191
00:14:42,430 --> 00:14:44,310
Dad! Wait!

192
00:14:44,470 --> 00:14:45,550
Calm down!

193
00:14:45,550 --> 00:14:47,030
Let me go!

194
00:14:47,430 --> 00:14:48,390
Dad!

195
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:54,030
God!

196
00:14:57,470 --> 00:14:58,550
Dad!

197
00:14:58,550 --> 00:14:59,670
Dad! Wait!

198
00:15:00,430 --> 00:15:02,220
[So, it changed my mind.]

199
00:15:02,220 --> 00:15:06,950
[It made me believe that soul mates were not real.]

200
00:15:06,950 --> 00:15:08,230
Dad!

201
00:15:11,150 --> 00:15:15,670
You thought that being someone's soul mate can be hurt.

202
00:15:18,550 --> 00:15:22,070
You really had a hard time.

203
00:15:23,230 --> 00:15:25,830
I did have a hard time.

204
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:31,510
How did you get through it?

205
00:15:37,790 --> 00:15:41,190
Well, I got this person, who is very kind,

206
00:15:42,830 --> 00:15:44,710
helped me all the way through,

207
00:15:44,710 --> 00:15:47,110
at every time I felt down.

208
00:15:47,910 --> 00:15:49,500
A kind person...

209
00:15:51,590 --> 00:15:53,910
Who's that? A he or she?

210
00:15:56,270 --> 00:15:57,670
I'm not telling you.

211
00:15:57,750 --> 00:15:58,870
What?

212
00:16:01,030 --> 00:16:02,310
Just kidding.

213
00:16:02,310 --> 00:16:04,390
I don't know who's that.

214
00:16:04,390 --> 00:16:06,070
I don't know what the person looks like.

215
00:16:06,630 --> 00:16:10,070
I knew that person from an acquaintance.

216
00:16:23,230 --> 00:16:25,270
Please turn left over there.

217
00:16:25,270 --> 00:16:26,510
Okay.

218
00:16:40,980 --> 00:16:42,660
Here we are.

219
00:16:55,390 --> 00:16:57,070
Thank you for driving me here.

220
00:16:57,430 --> 00:16:59,350
Have a good day.

221
00:16:59,950 --> 00:17:01,390
You, too.

222
00:17:04,390 --> 00:17:07,150
Wow! Someone drove Saengtai to work.

223
00:17:07,150 --> 00:17:08,630
A handsome man.

224
00:17:08,630 --> 00:17:11,630
-For a reserved guy, he's got a hot one.
-I know.

225
00:17:13,109 --> 00:17:14,180
Hello.

226
00:17:19,750 --> 00:17:21,230
I got to go.

227
00:17:21,510 --> 00:17:22,710
Okay.

228
00:17:35,310 --> 00:17:38,230
Hey!

229
00:17:38,230 --> 00:17:40,550
What's going on?

230
00:17:41,110 --> 00:17:43,230
Got something to tell me?

231
00:17:46,270 --> 00:17:50,190
If you don't tell me, I'll tell the boss you're going beyond your duty.

232
00:17:57,190 --> 00:17:58,590
What are you talking about, Bow?

233
00:17:59,550 --> 00:18:00,910
Don't you play dumb.

234
00:18:00,910 --> 00:18:03,030
Why the hot guy that day

235
00:18:03,030 --> 00:18:04,590
drive you here today? Huh?

236
00:18:04,590 --> 00:18:07,030
-Shush! -What?

237
00:18:09,830 --> 00:18:10,950
I have to work.

238
00:18:10,950 --> 00:18:11,510
Really?

239
00:18:11,510 --> 00:18:12,830
I'll take the stairs

240
00:18:12,830 --> 00:18:13,630
to do some exercise.

241
00:18:13,630 --> 00:18:14,350
Wait!

242
00:18:14,350 --> 00:18:16,230
Don't do that!

243
00:18:17,390 --> 00:18:19,590
How was it? What's up with him?

244
00:18:19,590 --> 00:18:20,750
He didn't tell me.

245
00:18:21,670 --> 00:18:24,510
Now, you go do your assignment that I gave you.

246
00:18:24,510 --> 00:18:27,510
If I get anything, I'll update to you guys.

247
00:18:27,830 --> 00:18:29,230
I must find it out.

248
00:18:29,230 --> 00:18:32,230
Because there's always one truth!

249
00:18:34,020 --> 00:18:35,830
Saengtai!

250
00:18:42,550 --> 00:18:43,790
Soul mate?

251
00:18:53,470 --> 00:18:54,590
Hold on.

252
00:18:55,660 --> 00:18:57,590
The guy's name is Patts.

253
00:18:58,470 --> 00:19:01,470
Your soul mate is a vet.

254
00:19:03,590 --> 00:19:06,590
Wow! It all comes together now!

255
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:11,150
And you said you were going to ignore your soul mate?

256
00:19:11,590 --> 00:19:15,550
I met him coincidentally .

257
00:19:17,430 --> 00:19:20,430
When it rained, I did ignore him.

258
00:19:21,390 --> 00:19:24,190
But when I met him,

259
00:19:25,870 --> 00:19:27,430
and talked to him,

260
00:19:28,020 --> 00:19:29,830
it turned out he's a really nice guy.

261
00:19:30,070 --> 00:19:32,710
So, I'll give it a try.

262
00:19:34,070 --> 00:19:36,230
Just a try?

263
00:19:36,230 --> 00:19:37,950
He's your soul mate!

264
00:19:38,430 --> 00:19:40,790
That's not just a try!

265
00:19:41,350 --> 00:19:43,070
I support you!

266
00:19:44,670 --> 00:19:45,950
Really.

267
00:19:45,950 --> 00:19:47,950
It's so difficult to meet him.

268
00:20:00,670 --> 00:20:02,870
May I get an iced americano?

269
00:20:04,830 --> 00:20:06,150
Who's that?

270
00:20:06,550 --> 00:20:07,790
Seangtien's friend.

271
00:20:09,510 --> 00:20:12,470
Wow. He's not bad.

272
00:20:13,820 --> 00:20:14,790
He's just a kid.

273
00:20:16,070 --> 00:20:19,110
I know. A kid is not my type.

274
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:25,230
But he's really pretty.

275
00:20:32,670 --> 00:20:33,910
Oops!

276
00:21:08,030 --> 00:21:09,030
Oh!

277
00:21:09,830 --> 00:21:13,830
Um, this is Bow, a friend from work.

278
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:16,950
And, this is Lomfon,

279
00:21:16,950 --> 00:21:18,110
Saengtien's friend.

280
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:19,430
Lomfon,

281
00:21:21,270 --> 00:21:23,630
nice to meet you!

282
00:21:23,630 --> 00:21:27,550
And, who's that girl? It's Bow.

283
00:21:30,070 --> 00:21:30,870
Hello.

284
00:21:33,950 --> 00:21:36,950
So lucky I didn't touch his hand.

285
00:21:40,910 --> 00:21:43,910
Are you doing a reserch for work?

286
00:21:44,790 --> 00:21:45,860
